  "original_title": "Sri Lanka gets 35,000 tourists up to August 28",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka gets 35,000 tourists up to August 28",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has welcomed only 480,000 tourists for the first 8 months with August arrivals so far-reaching 35,000, despite travel advisories, official data showed.",
        "Tourism arrival from August 1-28 is 35,381 with the top three source markets being UK, India and Germany.",
        "Almost 6,495 British travellers have visited Sri Lanka in August, followed by 5,015 Indians and 3,065 Germans.",
        "Despite the issues 1,293 Russians  have visited the country.",
        "Previously hoteliers said the bookings for the month were not encouraging and hotels across the island were seeing occupancy on average around 10-15 percent.",
        "In good years (pre-pandemic and Easter Sunday bombing), August was a month the island attracted large numbers of travellers for the various cultural festivals.",
        "From January first to August 23rd the country has welcomed 489,775 travelers.",
        "India has remained the top visitor for the first 8 months with 79,807 Indians visiting the country, followed by 65,374 British and at third place 49,614 Russians.",
        "Sri Lanka in mid-June said that it was targeting 800,000 travellers for the rest of the year with an estimated revenue of 800 million US dollars.",
        "The island has earned 824.9 million dollars for first seven months with 458,670 arrivals, according to central bank data. (Colombo/Aug31/2022)"
      ],
